NARRATIVE
Peer to Peer (P2P) file sharing allows people using P2P software to download and share files with other P2P users using the same or compatible P2P software. P2P software is readily available on the Internet and often free to download. Internet connected devices such as computers, tablets and smartphones running P2P software form a P2P network that allow users on the network to share digital files. BitTorrent is one of many P2P networks. For a user to become part of the BitTorrent network, the user must first obtain BitTorrent software and install it on a device. When the BitTorrent software is running and the device is connected to the Internet, the user will be able to download files from other users on the network and share files from their device with other BitTorrent users.

Users of the BitTorrent network wishing to share new content will use a BitTorrent program to create a “torrent” file for the file or group of files they wish to share. A torrent file is a small file that contains information about the file(s) and provides a method for a user to download the file(s) referenced in the torrent from other BitTorrent users. Torrent files are typically found as the result of keyword searches on Internet sites that host or link to them. Torrent files may be referenced by their “infohash”, which uniquely identifies the torrent based on the file(s) associated with the torrent file.

To download file(s) from other users on the BitTorrent network, a user typically obtains a torrent file. The BitTorrent software processes the information in the torrent file and locates devices on the BitTorrent network sharing all or parts or the actual file(s) being sought. The download of the content referenced in the torrent is achieved after the requesting computer and the sharing computer(s) directly connect to each other through the Internet using the BitTorrent software.

On 3/27/2023, TFC Mueller was conducting an online investigation on the BitTorrent network for offenders sharing child pornography. An investigation was initiated for a device at IP address 100.15.113.145, because it was associated with a torrent with the infohash: e8d2676709ebc062884330d51386fbf51445a26b. This torrent file references 57756 files, which were identified as being a file of investigative interest to child pornography investigations.

Using a computer running investigative BitTorrent software, a direct connection was made to the device at IP address 100.15.113.145, hereinafter referred to as “Suspect Device”. The Suspect Device reported it was using BitTorrent client software -TR3000-.

On 3/27/2023, between 1756 hrs and 1816 hrs, a download was successfully completed of the following 3 files that the device at IP address 100.15.113.145 was making available. The device at IP Address 100.15.113.145 was the sole candidate for each download, and as such, the file was downloaded directly from this IP Address.

File Name: lkd-020-083.jpg
Description: This color image depicts a young white female, nude, on a swing, exposing her breasts and vagina in a lewd and lascivious manner. The female is reasonably believed to be between 9-13 years old.

File Name: lkd-020-099.jpg
Description: This color image depicts a close up image of a young white female's vagina. It is responsibly believed to be of the same girl from file “lkd-020-083.jpg”.

File Name: lkd-020-085.jpg
Description: This color image depicts a young white female, nude, laying down, spreading her buttocks, exposing her vagina in a lewd and lascivious manner. The female is reasonably believed to be between 9-13 years old.

A check of "100.15.113.145" thorough Maxmind, shows the IP address is registered through Verizon Fios and geolocates to College Park, MD. On 4/3/2023 TFC Mueller authored a subpoena for subscriber information in reference to IP address “100.15.113.145”, and submitted it to the Howard County States Attorney’s Office for endorsement.

It should be noted a significant amount of downloads have occurred from the Suspect's Device, distributing Child Pornography and Child Erotica. 

On 4/4/2023 TFC Mueller received the endorsed Verizon subpoena. On 4/10/2023 TFC Mueller submitted the subpoena to Verizon. 

Case Open, investigation ongoing.

NARRATIVE:
   Since the initial investigation, I authored a search and seizure warrant for 5718 Vassar Drive, College Park, MD 20740.  On 8/28/2023, the SSW was signed by the Honorable Judge Wayne Brooks, Howard County District Court.

   On 8/29/2023 at approximately 0725 hrs, investigators from the MSP CCU, HSI and PGPD responded to the 5718 Vassar Drive, College Park, MD and executed the SSW.  Upon entry, contact was made with three occupants.  The residence was secured and searched for any electronic devices, as covered under the search and seizure warrant.  

The following subjects were interviewed:
HADI MOHAMMED-A ALZAYER DOB:10/13/1998
GAURANG SRIRAMANAN DOB: 11/24/1997
VASANTH PIDAPARTHY DOB: 4/18/1988

   TFC Mueller and I conducted interviews of the three listed subjects.  During the interview, all subjects were asked about their activity on any peer to peer networks.  All of them denied accessing any peer to peer networks or utilizing any file sharing programs related to this case.  They were asked about searching for, being sent, possessing or distributing child pornography, which they all denied.  They also informed us that there were two additional people living at the residence, who moved out prior to the execution of the search warrant.  They informed us they believe the two prior occupants moved out of state/country.  

 DFE Cobleigh and Herscher conducted on scene forensics of the devices located inside the residence.  No items of evidentiary value were located on those devices.  No items were seized from the residence.

Due to lack of evidence, this case is marked unfounded and closed.
